 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "12decec07298b653",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": "# Using probly with scikit-learn"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "id": "initial_id",
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2025-06-20T16:03:55.177409Z",
     "start_time": "2025-06-20T16:03:55.174057Z"
    },
    "collapsed": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "from sklearn.datasets import fetch_covtype\n",
    "from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier\n",
    "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
    "\n",
    "from probly.evaluation.tasks import selective_prediction\n",
    "from probly.quantification.classification import total_entropy"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "820f1fc023d8a352",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": "### Load the covertype dataset"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "id": "259012df07e9738f",
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2025-06-20T16:03:55.385480Z",
     "start_time": "2025-06-20T16:03:55.193391Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "data = fetch_covtype()\n",
    "X, y = data.data, data.target\n",
    "y = y - 1  # make the labels 0-indexed"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "39238145f1f07ffb",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": "### Fit a random forest"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "id": "fb4b3bc1c44204e7",
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2025-06-20T16:04:01.869754Z",
     "start_time": "2025-06-20T16:03:55.394953Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, test_size=0.3)\n",
    "# We set the max_depth to prevent obtaining only degenerate distributions.\n",
    "rf = RandomForestClassifier(n_estimators=20, max_depth=10)\n",
    "rf.fit(X_train, y_train)\n",
    "probs = [tree.predict_proba(X_test) for tree in rf.estimators_]\n",
    "# We need to change the order of the axes to match probly's convention of [n_instances, n_samples, n_classes]\n",
    "probs = np.array(probs).swapaxes(0, 1)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "efb2e588ef084171",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": "### Make an accuracy-rejection curve using total uncertainty"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "id": "b357b556ee2611d8",
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2025-06-20T16:04:01.923419Z",
     "start_time": "2025-06-20T16:04:01.874756Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "tu = total_entropy(probs)\n",
    "accuracies = (probs.mean(axis=1).argmax(axis=1) == y_test).astype(int)\n",
    "auc, bins = selective_prediction(tu, accuracies)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "id": "764c365e8b6113c1",
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2025-06-20T16:04:01.984889Z",
     "start_time": "2025-06-20T16:04:01.938858Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plt.plot(np.linspace(0, 1, len(bins)), bins)\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"Rejected Instances\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"Accuracy\")\n",
    "plt.title(f\"Accuracy-Rejection Curve, AUC: {auc:.3f}\")\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  }
 ],
